1
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:21,560
Miss Hu.

2
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:23,520
Marriage is not a joke.

3
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:25,000
You don't have to do this.

4
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:28,480
I already have a wife.

5
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:31,080
I won't be unfaithful.

6
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:33,720
Okay.

7
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:35,080
I understand.

8
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,400
But I won't give up.

9
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:45,160
Won't you try some?

10
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:46,620
It tastes pretty good.

11
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,860
I have no appetite.

12
00:01:55,479 --> 00:01:56,810
Why isn't Lord Yan here?

13
00:01:57,120 --> 00:02:00,250
You can't just see my adoptive father whenever you want.

14
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:03,960
The man and woman in the clinic,

15
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:05,240
how are they doing?

16
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:07,000
Ji Bai and Shen Yi.

17
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,400
They've been studying medicine at my clinic.

18
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,200
Nothing unusual has happened.

19
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:12,920
Shen Yi?

20
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:14,920
Are you saying

21
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:17,960
the man with the female doctor is named Shen Yi?

22
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:19,040
Yes.

23
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:20,370
Is something wrong?

24
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,920
Foster Father wants to know

25
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:27,600
about the mind-controlling insects you mentioned.

26
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,660
How is the development coming along?

27
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,640
I have completed the preliminary stage.

28
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:33,079
Give me a little more time.

29
00:02:33,079 --> 00:02:34,440
I will definitely finish it.

30
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:36,480
I must thank Lord Yan for the silver

31
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:37,740
and rare herbs he sent.

32
00:02:38,079 --> 00:02:39,520
They allowed me to create

33
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:41,090
the poisonous insects.

34
00:02:42,079 --> 00:02:42,920
In that case,

35
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,200
do not make a move on them for now.

36
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:47,410
Keep a close eye on their whereabouts.

37
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:49,320
Report to me if anything happens.

38
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:49,920
Yes.

39
00:02:50,079 --> 00:02:52,040
I will keep a close watch on them.

40
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:53,840
You may leave.

41
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,600
Wait.

42
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,040
Take this opportunity to investigate

43
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:00,680
Shen Yi's background.

44
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:01,320
Yes.

45
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:09,940
Foster Father.

46
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,340
You have done well.

47
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:13,480
You may leave.

48
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:14,320
Yes.

49
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:27,160
How does it feel?

50
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:40,400
I feel...

51
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,520
like it's a bit brighter.

52
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,240
That's great.

53
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:46,120
It seems your condition is improving.

54
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:47,360
As long as we continue treatment,

55
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:49,960
I believe your eyes will recover soon.

56
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:50,500
Really?

57
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:53,720
Can my eyes really be cured?

58
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:57,240
Thank you so much, Dr. Ji.

59
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,440
I don't know how to express

60
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:00,570
my gratitude to you.

61
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,280
I...

62
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:03,760
It's alright.

63
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,440
You're welcome.

64
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:08,560
It's my duty as a doctor.

65
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,360
However,

66
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:11,280
I have a few questions

67
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,600
I'd like to ask you.

68
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,280
Please ask.

69
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:16,440
I'll tell you everything I know.

70
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,880
Why were you in that cabin in the mountains?

71
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,080
When something happened to my family,

72
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:29,280
I fell off a cliff

73
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:30,580
and narrowly escaped.

74
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,240
Later,

75
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,240
I was injured and went blind.

76
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,680
A gentleman saved me.

77
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,330
And settled me in the cabin.

78
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:42,200
Who is that gentleman?

79
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:44,440
Why did he settle you there?

80
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:47,680
I...

81
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:50,000
I don't know who he is.

82
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,140
He was probably afraid

83
00:04:52,159 --> 00:04:53,440
I was being hunted.

84
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,680
So he let me hide there.

85
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:57,840
To recover in peace.

86
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:00,160
He visited me regularly.

87
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,860
And looked for famous doctors for me.

88
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:03,610
Then when was

89
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,200
the last time he visited?

90
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:07,200
About...

91
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,800
a month ago.

92
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:11,560
He brought me some rice and vegetables.

93
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,680
I see.

94
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:17,040
Miss Chuyun.

95
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:18,010
Don't worry.

96
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:20,080
I will do my best to cure your eyes.

97
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:22,000
But until then,

98
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,440
don't move around too much.

99
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,960
It might worsen your condition.

100
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:25,560
Okay.

101
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:27,720
I'll listen to you, Dr. Ji.

102
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:28,840
Thank you.

103
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,360
Dr. Ji,

104
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,800
you seem to

105
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:38,409
care about that person.

106
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:42,120
Because that cabin

107
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:45,120
was where a childhood friend lived.

108
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,360
So I suspect

109
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,120
the gentleman who saved you

110
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:50,520
is my long-lost friend.

111
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,520
Childhood friend?

112
00:06:01,880 --> 00:06:02,480
Hey.

113
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,280
I'm talking to you.

114
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:09,640
Can't you hear me?

115
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:11,600
I didn't hear you.

116
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:13,600
How dare you talk to me like that?

117
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:14,640
Don't you know

118
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,320
I'm the boss here?

119
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:19,240
I don't know you.

120
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:21,480
You dare look down on me?

121
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:22,760
Boys,

122
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:23,680
I'm going to teach

123
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:25,840
this arrogant brat a lesson.

124
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:28,880
You can't bully people.

125
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,080
Bully?

126
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,620
We're teaching her the rules.

127
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,760
You're obviously picking on the weak

128
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,840
and ganging up on her.

129
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:38,040
Where did this brat come from?

130
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,680
Daring to get in my way.

131
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:40,600
Get him!

132
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:51,080
Beat him to death if you dare.

133
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:53,659
But you'll pay for murder with your life.

134
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,400
Let's go.

135
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:57,680
Just you wait. I'll be back.

136
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,680
I came to help you.

137
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,900
But you just watched me get beaten up.

138
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,120
I can't beat them.

139
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,880
If I jumped in, we'd both just get beaten.

140
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,920
If I got hurt,

141
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:27,480
I wouldn't be able to treat your wounds.

142
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,240
You...

143
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,240
You're funny.

144
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,280
You have so many medical supplies.

145
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,480
Do you know medicine?

146
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,159
Just a little bit.

147
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,520
Come with me.

148
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:45,480
Divine Doctor Ji.

149
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:47,240
Divine Doctor Ji.

150
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:52,880
Actually,

151
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,600
this childhood friend and I,

152
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,159
when I was young,

153
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:59,159
shared a very deep bond.

154
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,680
But for some reason,

155
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,200
we were separated.

156
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:05,760
I see.

157
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,360
Could you tell me

158
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:08,960
stories about the two of you?

159
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:16,120
I grew up in the boudoir without any close friends.

160
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,320
So I am curious

161
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,800
how friends of the same age get along.

162
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,560
It's just some trivial stuff.

163
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,760
I don't mind telling you.

164
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,730
He is two years younger than me.

165
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,400
He loves crackers.

166
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,340
He was curious about everything.

167
00:08:35,679 --> 00:08:38,559
He'd often ask me about the mountain plants,

168
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,820
asking what they were.

169
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:54,340
This is Chinese angelica.

170
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:56,360
Sweet, acrid, and warm in nature.

171
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,860
It targets the Liver, Heart, and Spleen meridians.

172
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:05,640
You learn fast.

173
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:09,440
What are you thinking about?

174
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:14,280
I was thinking about the past with Jiujiu.

175
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,840
So you ran away from your wedding.

176
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,700
Was it also because of him?

177
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:27,180
How did you know I ran away from a wedding?

178
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:32,760
I...

179
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:36,840
You told me when you had that high fever.

180
00:09:37,280 --> 00:09:38,140
Did you forget?

181
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:43,880
It seems...

182
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:46,640
...I said things I shouldn't have.

183
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:48,760
It's fine.

184
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:50,640
Let's study the herbs again.

185
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,600
Tell me, is this honeysuckle

186
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,930
really that effective?

187
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,760
It not only clears heat and detoxifies,

188
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:58,890
but also promotes blood circulation.

189
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:05,280
That's all.

190
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:09,290
The time she spent with that childhood friend

191
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:10,770
doesn't seem very long.

192
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:11,520
Benefactor.

193
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:13,400
I don't think she's a bad person.

194
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,800
Is the person she's asking about

195
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:15,760
you?

196
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:19,600
Maybe.

197
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:20,560
I suppose.

198
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:23,560
Since you are Doctor Ji's childhood friend,

199
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,720
why don't you tell her?

200
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:28,690
Some things are hard to explain right now.

201
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:30,280
But rest assured,

202
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:32,560
I will tell her eventually.

203
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,000
What?

204
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:38,130
Don't you want to help me keep this secret?

205
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,600
How could I?

206
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,640
You must have your reasons.

207
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:46,000
Ever since you saved my life,

208
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,800
I've followed your lead in everything.

209
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,320
It's just...

210
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,560
You are childhood friends.

211
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,720
Your bond must be deep.

212
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:01,920
Alright.

213
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,080
You...

214
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,340
stop overthinking it.

215
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,840
I haven't seen her in years.

216
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:08,640
You

217
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,280
need to get some rest.

218
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,660
Let me apply the medicine.

219
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,080
These herbs

220
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,880
need to be spread out evenly,

221
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:35,480
so the sunlight can penetrate.

222
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,360
As for the others,

223
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,960
just place them in the shade.

224
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,210
Understood.

225
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,760
Angelica and Codonopsis need to be dried in the shade.

226
00:11:41,760 --> 00:11:42,680
Brother Shen,

227
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:43,840
Doctor Ji,

228
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:46,920
both of you,

229
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,000
come and sit.

230
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,000
Thanks for your hard work.

231
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,520
I brought some snacks

232
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,560
as a treat.

233
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,160
These are called Little Crispy Cakes.

234
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,600
I've loved them since I was young.

235
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,200
They look ordinary,

236
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,560
but they taste great.

237
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:13,100
They're actually quite good.

238
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:14,280
Try one.

239
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,960
I feel like I've had this somewhere before.

240
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:19,400
Wow. I didn't expect the herbs near my house

241
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,000
to sell for so much money.

242
00:12:32,240 --> 00:12:35,280
It is mainly because you and Master Lingyue know the value

243
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:37,160
that we could sell them for this much.

244
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,160
So, all this money is yours.

245
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:42,240
I'll just keep three coins as a runner's fee.

246
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:43,560
Okay.

247
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,120
Let's go.

248
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:47,800
I have money now.

249
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,600
I'll treat you to small crispy biscuits.

250
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:50,930
Small crispy biscuits.

251
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:52,280
They are my favorite.

252
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:54,140
You'll definitely like them too.

253
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,580
You've liked this since you were little.

254
00:13:35,640 --> 00:13:36,000
Liao, Chen, Luo, Deng,

255
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,600
Wu, Zhang, Li, Zheng, Chen, Luo, Deng,

256
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:36,720
Yi, Yi, Nan,

257
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:37,720
Xiao, Xiao, Xue, Yi, Yi, Nan,

258
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,120
Xiao, Xiao,

259
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,050
Xiao, Xiao, Xue.

260
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:06,160
Ma, Miao, Lu, Ran,

261
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,240
Ma, Miao, Lu, Ran.

262
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:11,600
Pan, Xiu, Long.

263
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:11,520
Lyu, Sun, Zhang, Meng,

264
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:11,920
Pan, Xiu,

265
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:12,840
Lyu, Sun, Zhang, Meng.
